# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Comment in the line below if you know you want it.
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in git.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a library/package, it should be ignored.
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in git.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in git.
#   pdm.lock

